The paper deals with the problem of making clusters more interpretable, which is a common goal in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computer science (cs.DS). The use of tags to associate objects with clusters suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the application of the proposed method to genomic sequences suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
